  "text": "The LC7 coding region was subcloned into the pMAL-c2 vector by PCRbased cloning (New England Biolabs Inc.) . This resulted in the COOHterminal fusion of LC7 to the maltose-binding protein via a hydrophilic linker containing a Factor Xa cleavage site. Expressed protein was purified by amylose affinity chromatography and the entire fusion protein was used to raise antisera in rabbit R7178. Subsequently, electrophoretically isolated recombinant LC7 was used to blot purify the antisera using the minor adaptions to the method of Olmsted (1986) described by [CITATION_1] .",
